        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9007.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 13 August 1873</ref> and n. 1. The reference is to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4584.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Richard Strachey</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9007.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 13 August 1873</ref> and n. 2. CD had noted that leaves and fruit were often protected by fine hairs or a waxy coating. <hi rend="italic">Nelumbium</hi> (now <hi rend="italic">Nelumbo</hi>) is the lotus genus.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Cryptogamia (non-flowering) and Phanerogamia (flowering) were former divisions of plants.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">For a summary of contemporary research on plant hairs (trichomes) and cuticular waxes, see Sachs 1873, pp. 85–8.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9007.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 13 August 1873</ref> and n. 4. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_203.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Acton Smee Ayrton</ref> was the former first commissioner of works, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5588.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Patrick Adam</ref> his successor; <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1791.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Douglas Strutt Galton</ref> was director of public works and buildings in the Office of Works (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5933.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi></ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Ayrton had been appointed judge-advocate-general (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5933.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi></ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f7">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9007.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 13 August 1873</ref> and n. 3. The reference is to <hi rend="italic">Oxalis sensitiva</hi> (a synonym of <hi rend="italic">Biophytum sensitivum</hi>).</note>
        </div>        
            
